race.comment: TYCOON DREAMER (7) showed enough in his debut campaign and her recent trial coming into this was very good. Parnham sticks from that trial and she looks ready to take the next step this campaign. Draw is iffy, but she can return on a positive note. MIDNIGHT DEAL (11) is on debut for the Grantham stable. She'll be aesthetically pleasing with Pike back in the cerise and white, taking the ride despite not trialling her leading in. She's bred to get over further, but she looks forward enough to put in a bold effort on debut. PLAYA DEL SOL (9) never really got into the race on debut at Northam and returns to the races without a trial coming in. That is the query, though the booking of Brad Parnham is a good sign and she can put her best foot forward. DESERT ORA (8) flew home on debut at 100-1 and the rise in trip should suit. Has to be included. UNIVERSAL DUKE (5) trialled nicely coming into this and can feature in the finish.
